reviews.review:
I'm just your average movie fan, 

I've been able to watch movies for free and I can say Knives out was pretty good movie. 

I think the chemistry with the actors was well, I think it did a great job with the mystery. It reminds me of a Sherlock Holmes but the book version on film. It had pretty good humor and it had you wondering if you are being tricked yourself.

Overall the movie has some well known heavy actors, so the acting was not an issue in my opinion, but not the best mystery movies I've seen but it was interesting , it had a good amount of soft humor and some action. 

if you are into mystery movies then you would enjoy watching thins in movie theater, may not be your favorite but worth it. If you not a big mystery crime movie fan then this would be great Netflix or red box.

Maybe a Spoiler: But I think this is first mystery movie I didn't predict the ending because it wasn't trying to be so mysterious that you actually could tell what was going to happen, I think the ending is so predictable you wouldn't predict it, but in a good way...

Also I didnt fall inlove with main character, she was sweet but I wasnt rooting for her as much as for the detective and the father, but you always wanted her to out do the family, so she was likable in that manner.
you'll laugh, you'll cry, you'll find out who dun it
The whole theater erupted with applause when this movie was over. So fun!

Great cast and a plot that keeps you guessing until the end. Side notes: Daniel Craigs southern accent was pretty convincing. And Chris Evans playing a total jerk was a fun change of pace.
Slow.  Wife and I struggled to stay awake.  We contemplated leaving but the $50 on tix and popcorn was hard to just walk out.  At least the popcorn was good.
Great murder mystery. Great cast. Seems slow at times but for the most part the pace is good. Nice to have a decent option at the movies which not easy to find imo.

Great acting, great cast, fun at all angles. You think you know whats going on but then it flips on you. Daniel Craig was a blast if you love Sherlock Holmes and Chris Evans adds a lil spice to the mix up.
Great who dun it with a twist & a cast full of old favorites.
